Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.57,0:01:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The US Navy, which has won the Battle of Midway and gained momentum,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.26,0:01:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was about to launch a counterattack against the Japanese in order to take control of the Pacific War.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.14,0:02:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On August 6th, 1942, a fleet of 31 ships carrying 19,000 Marines was secretly heading north into the South Pacific,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.70,0:02:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,protected by approximately 60 escort ships centered on three aircraft carriers and one battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.07,0:02:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Savo Island (Episode 13)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.18,0:02:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the Tulagi and Guadalcanal campaigns
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.27,0:02:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is primarily to enable contact between the United States and Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.42,0:02:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, it was a stepping stone to control Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.10,0:02:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, it would prevent the Japanese troops from moving further south.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the reconnaissance aircraft reports,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.06,0:02:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,no planes have yet arrived at the Japanese airfield under construction at Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they can come from Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.77,0:02:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For that purpose, there is a coast watcher of the Royal Australian Navy Intelligence Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.94,0:03:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These coast watchers are farmers, pastors, officials, miners, etc. who were mobilized to protect the vast Australian coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.86,0:03:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They lurked in the jungle with the local people, and were in charge of informing every movement of the Japanese army .
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.76,0:03:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The distance from Rabaul to Tulagi and Guadalcanal is about 560 nautical miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy can only fly over us for 20 or 30 minutes at the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it will take at least four days for our army to complete the landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.96,0:03:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the enemy makes an attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We have already lost Lexington in the Coral Sea and Yorktown at Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.08,0:03:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we lose more aircraft carriers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Aircraft carriers are vulnerable to bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.91,0:03:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As the landing commander, I cannot kill 20,000 Marines.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.36,0:03:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I need the support of an aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.92,0:03:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not just saying that as a commander of the aircraft carrier fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.04,0:04:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If two of the three remaining aircraft carriers in the Pacific, or even one, are killed, the war is lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.99,0:04:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you should cancel such an operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell General Nimitz or Vice Admiral Ghormley in Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.02,0:04:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't get so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.74,0:04:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation has already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.02,0:04:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, why don't you carry out the landing operation as planned and then reconsider after seeing the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.73,0:04:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you not scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I try not to think about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.37,0:04:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not Tarzan. Can you fight these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese soldiers can dive for miles while sucking air from trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.34,0:05:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Barefoot, no noise in the jungle, climbs trees like a monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.15,0:05:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Evil, ascetic, and able to travel farther than we do. They can survive with a small amount of food and endure any pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really scared too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.45,0:05:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not ordinary human beings. They are werewolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,On August 7th, at 3:00 am,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.62,0:05:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the American transport fleet approaching Cape Esperance, northwest of Guadalcanal Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,split into two parts across Savo Island at the entrance of the narrow strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.08,0:05:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Protected by the escort fleet, and Guadalcanal Island. They approached Cape Lunga and Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, on Guadalcanal Island, the construction of an airfield for the Japanese army had been completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.17,0:06:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the 6th Air Group, Misawa Air Group, and Mitsubishi G4M Corps
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are scheduled to fly from Rabaul to this Guadalcanal airfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.12,0:06:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, the airfield construction team will conduct pilot training, Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.45,0:06:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.74,0:06:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.85,0:06:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.30,0:06:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, the Japanese defense force of Guadalcanal was about 2000 members of the construction team
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.44,0:06:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and 203 members of the Japanese land squadron. And there were 700 Japanese troops in Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The US-Australian fleet attacked seaplane bases on Guadalcanal and Tulagi on Florida, and began landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.66,0:06:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Headquarters predicted that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the US military would rebound in the latter half of 1943, given its military strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the counterattack was faster than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.20,0:07:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the Rabaul air base on the Japanese side that received this news.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately raise all troops and attack the invading enemy units.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the enemy's intention is a reconnaissance in force or the destruction of the airfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.44,0:07:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,#Missing Line
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,2nd unit, 27 Mitsubish G4Ms, 1st unit, 18 Zero fighters for 07:30, 3rd unit, 9 aircraft, start as soon as ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.76,0:07:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, after the Battle of Midway, the 8th Fleet, the combined fleet under the command of Vice Admiral Mikawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.88,0:07:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was about to head to Guadalcanal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.14,0:08:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The distance from Rabaul to Guadalcanal is just about Shimonoseki from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot expect much success from our military airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However, our fleet has just been formed and has not yet taken any fleet action.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.94,0:08:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, since it is such a distance, there is a good chance that it will be attacked by enemy aircraft on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.30,0:08:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm prepared for that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.24,0:08:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the battle of Midway, our navy has been too cowardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.44,0:08:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the opinion of Chief Yamamoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He agrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.86,0:08:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do so with the free discretion given to the fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.06,0:08:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,even if opposed by the Imperial Headquarters or the Combined Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.92,0:08:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.54,0:08:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you, Chief of Staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.64,0:08:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If the chief is so determined, then I will not dissent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.74,0:08:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.96,0:08:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Decide what to do later based on the result of the land based air reconnaissance and attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.15,0:09:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.64,0:09:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Senior Staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have never sailed the surface of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's a rough strategy, so there is no choice but to make it rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.45,0:09:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, this is the first fleet night battle in the history of this world war. Let's do it roughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The flagship, and the 6th Fleet, will sortie immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For the Japanese side, being deprived of Guadalcanal would be a serious threat to the New Guinea area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.75,0:10:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,24 bombers, head toward Tuvalu and Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.64,0:10:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This information was sent to the headquarters of the Hawaii Pacific Fleet, and was forwarded to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the US operational unit sailing near Guadalcanal Island by strong radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.30,0:10:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship is scheduled to be attacked by 24 enemy aircraft at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The upper right sky, enemy aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.54,0:11:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Good
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The damage suffered by the Japanese side in this battle was five land based attack aircraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.22,0:11:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,five shipboard bombers, and two Zero fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.76,0:11:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The damage to the US and Australian army was 11 fighters, one dive bomber, and the destroyer McMurdo was sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.66,0:12:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is the enemy aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.13,0:12:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we have to be prepared for an invasion of enemy aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.55,0:12:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens, and there are no aircraft carriers here, then we may be wiped out. {Not quite sure what is happening here, seems like they are continuing each other's sentences. HA has it as one line though }
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.68,0:12:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be discovered by the enemy at all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.18,0:12:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that will beat the enemy is a surprise attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.65,0:12:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Right front, enemy patrol!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.60,0:12:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, pretend to head northwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.66,0:12:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Full port. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.79,0:12:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy patrol aircraft has disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Restore our course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.70,0:13:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of you gather in the operation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.43,0:13:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We passed through the Bougainville Strait and broke through the central waterway at high speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.90,0:13:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Rush from the right side of Savo Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.17,0:13:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,First, a surprise attack will be made to the ships moored in Guadalcanal, then the enemy of Tulagi will be attacked,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.91,0:13:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the enemy planes will hurry back to a point where they cannot be attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.70,0:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy patrol aircraft, 90 degrees to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.94,0:13:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Cruisers three, destroyers three,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.19,0:14:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,seaplane tenders two, course 120 degrees, speed 15 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.92,0:14:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Persistent guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to change direction again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes too much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.64,0:14:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, threaten them with an 8-inch gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.42,0:14:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, there is no doubt that enemy planes will come in a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.28,0:14:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Start each aircraft and scout the enemy's condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Each ship should have a strict anti-aircraft lookout.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.26,0:15:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the reconnaissance officer belonging to the Royal Australian Air Force,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who discovered the Japanese fleet, continued to scout the area they were charged with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.59,0:15:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At around 2:30 pm, they returned to their base in Milne Bay, on the southern tip of New Guinea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.36,0:15:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They then reported the formation of the Japanese fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.70,0:15:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,unconfirmed to MacArthur's Command in Townsville, Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.92,0:15:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a delay of nearly 8 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.68,0:16:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently we are okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I have never had a day as long as today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.46,0:16:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We will surely win tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm giving instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.87,0:16:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.87,0:16:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Instruction: Win and rush into the night battle, Which is a tradition of the Imperial Japanese Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.64,0:16:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Be calm and do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.88,0:16:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Admiral Ghormley.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.91,0:17:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We have finished the mission of landing support,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We have finished the mission of landing support,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.19,0:17:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,21 out of 99 carrier-based aircraft were lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.51,0:17:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,21 out of 99 carrier-based aircraft were lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.93,0:17:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to the large number of enemy bombers and torpedo bombers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.22,0:17:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems appropriate for our fleet to withdraw immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.34,0:17:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There is also a shortage of fuel, so we must request that a refueling ship be dispatched as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.19,0:17:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there was still four days worth of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.32,0:17:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the American side pulled out their escort fleet, including the aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.78,0:17:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Fletcher decided he didn't want to risk losing his aircraft carrier anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.54,0:17:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,now that he lost Lexington and Yorktown in the two battles of the Coral Sea and Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.38,0:18:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from Aoba's reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.82,0:18:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Three enemy cruisers patrolling Savo Island, and southwestern sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.87,0:18:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, from now on, we will rush to the berth on Guadalcanal Island
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.66,0:18:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with a speed of 30 knots and a course of 95 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,10 degrees to the right, three cruisers. Going to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Illumination!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.22,0:18:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,#Missing Line
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,#Missing Line
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.55,0:18:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.33,0:19:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.52,0:19:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,#Missing Line
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.70,0:19:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.40,0:19:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a major victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.70,0:19:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately change course to the left and run the troops off Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.04,0:21:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently its 00:10. Feel free to give your opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.92,0:21:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We should withdraw immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.04,0:21:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There are few torpedoes and an enemy task force is believed to be near San Crisbal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.80,0:21:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is distance and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.09,0:21:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes two hours to reorganize the fleet and reach Lunga Point, no matter how urgent it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's past 4o'clock, its morning on the Solomon Sea, so
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.34,0:21:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it is impossible to escape from the enemy aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Two hours
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy convoy should be naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.26,0:21:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The chief also said. If we were discovered by an aircraft carrier, our force would be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.41,0:22:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Withdraw the entire force.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.96,0:22:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Course 320 degrees. speed 30 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,However, at that time, the American aircraft carrier had left far away from Guadalcanal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.71,0:22:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, let's go attack again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.22,0:22:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If we go only with Chokai, we can escape fast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.68,0:22:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you leave the convoy, your enemies will only get fat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.62,0:22:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, a well supplied enemy will affect future operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.31,0:23:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot lose an important warship by making a reckless attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.52,0:23:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the first night battle in the history of naval battles in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.40,0:23:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,ended with a one-sided victory for the Japanese side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.79,0:23:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Guadalcanal’s American convoy was left unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.58,0:23:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Given replenishment of troops, ammunition, and food has a major impact on the final victory, was this decision correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.74,0:23:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When making a decision, always look to the future and do not lose sight of the big picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.86,0:23:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,without hesitation about the immediate victory or damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.88,0:23:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This naval battle, which brought victory to the Japanese side,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.19,0:23:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,was one of the major causes of the upcoming tragedy of Guadalcanal.
